    <name>
      <text>Calculating Areas of a Mechanical Arm Sweep</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>A mechanical arm sweeps through \({@theta@}\). The outer radius is \({@R@}\,\text{m}\) and the inner radius is \({@r@}\,\text{m}\). Calculate the following areas:</p>

<ol type='a'>
    <li>
        <p>The area of the smaller circle formed by the arm. [[input:ans1]]\(\,\text{m}^2\) [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p>
          
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>The area of the larger circle formed by the arm. [[input:ans2]]\(\,\text{m}^2\)[[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>The area of the region swept by the mechanical arm. [[input:ans3]]\(\,\text{m}^2\) [[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]]</p>
    </li>
</ol>



<p></p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<ol type='a'>
    <li>
        <p><strong>Area of the smaller circle (inner radius):</strong></p>
        <p>
        \(\begin{align}
        A_{\text{inner}} &= \pi r^2 \\
        &= \frac{22}{7} \times ({@r@})^2 \\
        &= {@A_inner_3sf@}\ \text{m}^2
        \end{align}\)
        </p>
    </li>

    <li>
        <p><strong>Area of the larger circle (outer radius):</strong></p>
        <p>
        \(\begin{align}
        A_{\text{outer}} &= \pi R^2 \\
        &= \frac{22}{7} \times ({@R@})^2 \\
        &= {@A_outer_3sf@}\ \text{m}^2
        \end{align}\)
        </p>
    </li>

    <li>
        <p><strong>Area of the region swept by the mechanical arm:</strong></p>
        <p>
        \(\begin{align}
        A_{\text{swept}} &= \frac{\theta}{360} \pi (R^2 - r^2) \\
        &= \frac{@theta@}{360} \times \frac{22}{7} \times \left( {@R@}^2 - {@r@}^2 \right) \\
        &= {@A_swept_3sf@}\ \text{m}^2
        \end{align}\)
        </p>
        <p>Alternatively, you can subtract the area of the inner circle from the area of the outer circle the multiply by \(\frac{{@theta@}}{360}\):</p>
        <p>
        \(\begin{align}
        A_{\text{swept}} &= ({@A_outer_3sf@} - {@A_inner_3sf@})\times \frac{{@theta@}}{360} \\
        &= {@swept@}\ \text{m}^2\\
&={@A_swept_3sf@}\ \text{m}^2
        \end{align}\)
        </p>
    </li>
</ol>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
